<taxonomicName id="F77E438CB604635AAA9050AADC029490" LSID="673E4191-B2F7-52F6-B9C3-CE439A8FCF10" authority="(Broth.) H. Rob. &amp; G. K. Golinski" authorityName="H. Rob. &amp; G. K. Golinski" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="H. Rob. &amp; G. K. Golinski" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Brachymenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachymenium perspinidens" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perspinidens" status="comb. nov.">Brachymenium perspinidens (Broth.) H.Rob. &amp; G.K.Golinski</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5056F4CFB2E6EEC17C59289D0E401CFB" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<figureCitation id="58C72EE3F837AD61ECE818977A2EAC33" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Brachymenium ayangannensis H. Rob. &amp; G. K. Golinski. A Leafy stem showing distorted leaves B distal part of leaves, showing well-developed pale margin and spiniform teeth on both margin and long-acuminate tip C remoistened erect capsule showing partially detached short-rostrate operculum D B. perspinidens (Broth.) H. Rob. &amp; Golinski, distal part of leaf of holotype (from H) E tip of capsule mounted in Hoyer's solution showing short exostome and lack of well-developed endostome. The photographs were taken using a Leica DM 4 B Compound microscope, using a 5 x objective." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.154.39105.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/438302" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Figure 1D</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4B1065F885254E21F13F50D93EE77AFB" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="FF67094FBF932A781D6DBEE92A3837EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="866F8B12E1EE1295C6E7C39A475CB789" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum perspinidens" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perspinidens">Bryum perspinidens</taxonomicName>
Broth., Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 24: 246. 1897. Britische Ostafrika, Seengebiet: Ru- Nssóro, 3300-3600 m (Uganda: Ruwenzori, heather forest 10-12000'), 
<emphasis id="27B6BC062CF7B8D616708882D3143B6A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Scott Elliot 266</emphasis>
, Sterile. 
<taxonomicName id="C4383133BF0D169AF6023FF988E57E2F" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Rhodobryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhodobryum perspinidens" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perspinidens">Rhodobryum perspinidens</taxonomicName>
(Broth.) Pócs, in Bizot &amp; Pócs, Acta Bot. Acad. Sci. Hungaricae 25: 257. 1979 [1980]. With record of species from Tanzania, also sterile. 
<bibRefCitation id="D67EBA45A5922E812250B837383AA5D8" author="Ochi, H" journalOrPublisher="Tottori University" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 126" refId="B8" refString="Ochi, H, 1972. A revision of African Bryoideae, Musci (First Part). J. Faculty of Educ. Tottori University 23 (1): 1 - 126" title="A revision of African Bryoideae, Musci (First Part). J. Faculty of Educ." volume="23" year="1972">Ochi (1972)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the species was rather an oddity in 
<taxonomicName id="0FD697EBCC1AF678B870AFE78A7BC6D0" authority="Rhodobryum" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum (Rhodobryum) subsp. subgenus" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="subGenus" species="perspinidens" subGenus="Rhodobryum" subSpecies="subgenus">Bryum Hedw. subgenus Rhodobryum</taxonomicName>
Schimp. in which he placed it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="234D804ED5601DFEA005B652F540A6A9" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="notes">
<paragraph id="059A5DE15E89878242D16A18FB7EA896" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="02A38888BEF540D472DBBC201C569FE6" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
Placement of the new species in 
<taxonomicName id="AF9B14667BD9DC1997492887FAF5C555" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Brachymenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachymenium" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E5382BA9FB8B24B3A75E65DB350420FF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Brachymenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on the capsules being erect with an inner peristome being a low membrane lacking segments or cilia, the traditional distinctions of the genus. Recent DNA studies (
<bibRefCitation id="A24A09D6334390C17CF20A6811560518" author="Pedersen, N" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="471 - 482" refId="B11" refString="Pedersen, N, Cox, CJ, Hedenas, L, 2003. Phylogeny of the Moss Family Bryaceae Inferred from Chloroplast DNA Sequences and Morphology. Systematic Botany 28 (3): 471 - 482" title="Phylogeny of the Moss Family Bryaceae Inferred from Chloroplast DNA Sequences and Morphology." volume="28" year="2003">Pedersen et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="668AD9BDD8EFCFE212F702CFBB72E7CC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1639/0007-2745(2005)108[123:TANIOP]2.0.CO;2" author="Pedersen, N" journalOrPublisher="Scientiae Naturales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" refId="B10" refString="Pedersen, N, Hedenas, L, 2005. Taxonomic and Nomenclatural Implications of Phylogenetic Studies of the Bryaceae Based on Molecular Data and Morphology. The Bryologist 108(1): 123-128. https://doi.org/10.1639/0007-2745(2005)108[123:TANIOP]2.0.CO;2" title="Taxonomic and Nomenclatural Implications of Phylogenetic Studies of the Bryaceae Based on Molecular Data and Morphology. The Bryologist 108 (1): 123 - 128." url="https://doi.org/10.1639/0007-2745(2005)108[123:TANIOP]2.0.CO;2" year="2005">Pedersen and Hedenas 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BCD195E71CA7C58769412BF7E0CA1F7B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1179/037366803125002635" author="Cox, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bryology" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="31 - 40" refId="B6" refString="Cox, CJ, Hedderson, AJ, 2003. Phylogenetic relationships within the moss family Bryaceae based on chloroplast DNA evidence. Journal of Bryology 25 (1): 31 - 40, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1179/037366803125002635" title="Phylogenetic relationships within the moss family Bryaceae based on chloroplast DNA evidence." url="https://doi.org/10.1179/037366803125002635" volume="25" year="2003">Cox and Hedderson 2003</bibRefCitation>
) indicate that species that have been placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="83A515136B18A076E1A7F808103A9992" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Brachymenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachymenium" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="062E47A97E0D2F0448C395E802D5817C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Brachymenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are mostly in basal branches of the 
<taxonomicName id="391DD775178EBF8C69618688F9CFCC23" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Brachymenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="family">Bryaceae</taxonomicName>
while 
<taxonomicName id="3C4F5C4F8148B29B6F6D5B35B342F86B" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3540A5F70B139D727BC4053532C1CBF0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Bryum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are more derived. According to such studies, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8AE6B4CB0001886613A2D8B0DCA1BCEC" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Brachymenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachymenium" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FAF1B338D71AB6AE94073DE2B07BE9E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Brachymenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more entangled phyletically with the genus 
<taxonomicName id="49B0A919BD84EF240FF851D6EE72BE7F" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Rhodobryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhodobryum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16FEC2EC11CE118F7804931E27641463" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Rhodobryum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schimp.) Hampe, Linnaea 38: 663. 1874, a later established genus and 
<taxonomicName id="603BAB7BEBAB382B98E7050E341F0724" authority="De Notaris, 1859" authorityName="De Notaris" authorityYear="1859" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Osculatia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Osculatia" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="37FCC7B0FFD7D8C8ED613E7473B7FCB9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Osculatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
De Not., Mem. Reale Accad. Sci. Torino, ser 2, 18: 445. 1859 (
<bibRefCitation id="25946DBF1EA28EE18E4E9B7A3194FDD4" author="Robinson, H" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Venezuelica" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="73 - 83" publicationUrl="https://www.jstor.org/stable/41740407" refId="B12" refString="Robinson, H, 1965. Venezuelan bryophytes collected by Julian Steyermark. Acta Botanica Venezuelica 1 (1): 73 - 83, https://www.jstor.org/stable/41740407" title="Venezuelan bryophytes collected by Julian Steyermark." url="https://www.jstor.org/stable/41740407" volume="1" year="1965">Robinson 1965</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3E037D6D87F37213DFCD780B9D851895" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2478/cszma-2018-0006" author="Ochyra, R" journalOrPublisher="Scientiae Naturales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="71 - 79" refId="B9" refString="Ochyra, R, Plasek, V, Bednarek-Ochyra, H, 2018. Osculatia -an earlier name for a segregate of Bryum (Bryaceae, Bryophyta). Acta Musei Silesiae. Scientiae Naturales 67 (1): 71 - 79, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2478/cszma-2018-0006" title="Osculatia - an earlier name for a segregate of Bryum (Bryaceae, Bryophyta). Acta Musei Silesiae." url="https://doi.org/10.2478/cszma-2018-0006" volume="67" year="2018">Ochyra et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). A survey of the illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation id="D77D323886ED0B8FD293680576DD74EC" author="Brotherus, VF" editor="Engler, A" journalOrPublisher="I. TEIL, 3, Abteilung, Bogen 37 bis 39. Verlag von Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="577 - 624" refId="B4" refString="Brotherus, VF, 1904. 219 Lieferung, Bryaceae, Leptostomaceae, Mniaceae, Rhizogoniaceae und Aulacomniaceae. In: Engler, A, Prantl, K, Eds., Die natuerlichen Pflanzenfamilien. I. TEIL, 3, Abteilung, Bogen 37 bis 39. Verlag von Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig: 577 - 624" title="219 Lieferung, Bryaceae, Leptostomaceae, Mniaceae, Rhizogoniaceae und Aulacomniaceae." volumeTitle="Die natuerlichen Pflanzenfamilien." year="1904">Brotherus (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0CE1DF650016EAD27F64E0AD0B7256C6" author="Brotherus, VF" journalOrPublisher="In: Engler A, Prantl (Eds) Die natuerlichen Pflanzenfamilien, ed. 2. 10" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" refId="B5" refString="Brotherus, VF, 1925. Musci (Laubmoose) 1 Hafte. In: Engler A, Prantl (Eds) Die natuerlichen Pflanzenfamilien, ed. 2. 10" title="Musci (Laubmoose) 1 Hafte." year="1925">1925</bibRefCitation>
) shows an additional trend in 
<taxonomicName id="55872777A79853B985DC35456BAE2B2F" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Brachymenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachymenium" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CEC3E709B90B631A8BF98A54B52D8BB0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Brachymenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is lacking in typical 
<taxonomicName id="26EF346B471644A206021FA73EAD6D3D" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3929817A3212C45073EFBE3A6C296710" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Bryum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, conical to rostrate opercula such is seen in the new species. In fact, within the present definition of 
<taxonomicName id="1C25EE4E499A646EC96ADA486E07C9A9" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Brachymenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brachymenium" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7378E081917D7B4A14D5F7275AFF4877" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Brachymenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, fully rostrate opercula occur in another species recently collected in Guyana.
</paragraph>
